<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Anglogold says half workforce away Monday.</title>
<headline>Anglogold says half workforce away Monday.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-06-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Anglogold, South Africa's largest gold producer, said about half its workforce had reported for work on Monday, a better turnout than expected in the face of a call for a one-day general strike.</p>
<p>&quot;Nevertheless, the resultant production losses -- in a climate dominated by the low gold price and lower production due to public holidays earlier in the quarter -- are most unwelcome,&quot; a spokesman said.</p>
<p>Anglogold produced 50.2 kg of gold in the three months to March 31, 1997.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom, +27 11 482-1003</p>
